"if you watched the entire election cycle and concluded that trump was nothing but a lucky clown, you missed one of the most important perceptual shifts in the history of humankind. i'll fix that for you in this book." adams was one of the earliest public figures to predict trump’s win, doing so a week after nate silver put trump’s odds at 2 percent in his fivethirtyeight.com blog. the mainstream media regarded trump as a novelty and a sideshow. but adams recognized in trump a level of persuasion you only see once in a generation.  trump triggered massive cognitive dissonance and confirmation bias on both the left and the right. we’re hardwired to respond to emotion, not reason. we might listen to 10 percent of a speech—a hand gesture here, a phrase there—and if the right buttons are pushed, we decide we agree with the speaker and invent reasons to justify that decision after the fact.  the point isn’t whether trump was right or wrong, good or bad. win bigly goes beyond politics to look at persuasion tools that can work in any setting—the same ones adams saw in steve…

text:
as a california business, i hope you are on top of your sexual harassment prevention training requirements for all your managers. however, this year california expanded training requirements to your non-supervisory employees as well. new senate bill 1343 ("sb 1343") also extends training requirements to all the companies with five or more employees. 
sb 1343 requires covered employers to provide at least two hours of sexual harassment prevention training to all supervisory employees and at least one hour of  training to all non-supervisory employees by january 1, 2020. training and education must be provided once every two years after that, as specified under the new law.
also, employers must provide sexual harassment prevention training to temporary or seasonal employees within 30 calendar days after the hire date or within 100 hours worked if the employee will work for less than six months. in the case of a temporary employee employed by a temporary services employer (as defined by the california labor code) to perform services for clients, the training must be provided by the temporary services employer, not the client. the anti-sexual harassment training may be conducted with other employees, as a group, or individually, and broken up into shorter time segments, as long as the two-hour requirement for supervisory employees and the one-hour requirement for non-supervisory employees is reached.
 #sb1343 #metoo #hr #sexualharassment #training #california #employees #entreprenuer #business #doingbusinessinca #eastwestgeneralcounsel

text:
more humans registered for a dating app yesterday than any other day.  and a lot of the women i talk to make a dramatic sigh when i mention dating apps. 
and yet, more and more single women are saying, “i’m good, thanks”. they’ve read the books, taken the online courses, made the lists....and still keep meeting the same assholes in different meat suits. 
so what’s missing? 
these are smart, successful, beautiful women.  and they’re reluctantly leaving the dating scene. “it’s just not for me”
“my healer/coach/psychic told me i’m being punished this lifetime”

i call bullshit.  but i get the frustration, i really do.  still, if you take a slow exhale and ask your heart if any of those things are true i bet you a bulletproof coffee they are not. 
so what’s missing? 
here’s a secret- the only difference between the women who are finding the love of their lives and the women frustrated, irritated and ready to throw in the towel?

the only difference is healing the second chakra. 
yes, it’s the sex chakra. 
but it’s also the seat of creativity and emotions and sensuality.  and when we heal, and play and do the work to have a constant flow? 
magic. 
it is possible.  you are not a lost cause.  the secrets to the universe and relationships were not given to everyone else but you. 
you are not missing a key ingredient. 
and there’s nothing you need to change to get there. 
breathe. 
before you go trying to change one more thing about yourself

stop.  breathe.  and look around for someone who embodies what you want.  because your person is going to want you.  all of you.  the good the bad and the quirky. 
let’s go find you 😊❤️💗🌈
if you want more sign up for the goddess club- 3-4 emails a week designed to inspire you, align you and find....you.

text:
i just have to give a special shout out to this man right here! 😭⁣
⁣
i can’t tell you every detail of this transformation and awakening i’m going through yet, but i can tell you that this man is seeing more of it than anyone else. ⁣
⁣
he’s supported my super slow mornings of reflection, journaling and coffee sipping in bed that can last hours. ⁣
⁣
he’s listened to me talk about my soul in some crazy ways, that though he doesn’t quite understand fully yet, he smiles and accepts me. ⁣
⁣
he’s watched me as i’ve released old trauma, old patterns and low frequencies. ⁣
⁣
he’s loved me on everyday of this new journey i’m on and never once questioned the soul work i’m doing even though it’s not what our old norm used to be. ⁣
⁣
loving, supportive and handsome are the best words to describe this man of mine.⁣
⁣
babe, you’ll never know how much i truly love you because it’s an indescribable love, but i’ll spend my whole life trying to show you. ♥️⁣

there are so many topics and words i want to dive into this year... i almost don’t know where to start... but everything seems to fit one specific theme... a program or code... a set of beliefs... that govern our every thought and move...
✏️
our modern society with all its rules and taboos... has given me endless material to examine... but under all those systems... there is a cycle of nature... that’s what intrigues me the most...
🌱
empowering my voice... one of a female... i thrilled to be living at a time when... we can truly honor everything about a woman... and at 43... i can release all the guilt and shame of what it’s meant to be a woman in the last couple thousand years... and uncover the true science and mystery of the womb... and female energy... without it being put in a corner... etc etc...
🧡
if you have or love a #yoni please share a tip... and make talking about menstration more open... while i go research the etymology of it...

text:
after serving 15 years in prison, cyntoia brown will be released on aug. 7 and will remain on parole for 10 years. brown, an alleged sex trafficking victim serving a life sentence for the 2004 murder of a man who picked her up and took her to his home, was 16 years old when she committed the crime in what she described as an act of self-defense.
•
brown’s story spread widely in the fall of 2017 amid the #metoo movement. supporters rallied around her case with the hashtag #freecyntoiabrown, calling it an example of the country’s unjust incarceration of children and victims of sex trafficking. kim kardashian highlighted the case to president trump in a meeting last may over prison reform. “i am thankful for all the support, prayers, and encouragement i have received,” brown said. “we truly serve a god of second chances and new beginnings.”
•
while in prison, brown has earned her ged and an associate degree with a 4.0 gpa, according to a statement from tennessee gov. bill haslam. she has one course left to complete her bachelor’s degree, which she expects to finish in may of this year. “with god’s help, i am committed to live the rest of my life helping others, especially young people,” brown said. “my hope is to help other young girls avoid ending up where i have been.” (photo by lacy atkins/tennessean/ap; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
it’s finally time to bring ‘beneath the veil’ into the world 🌹

you can pre-order your copy now and be holding her in your hands in two weeks! ✨

www.bernadetteoconnor.com/sales (linkinbio)

beneath the veil is the spellbinding new novel from bestselling author, bernadette o’connor, recounting the story of clara, and her quest for truth, freedom and wisdom. ‘many a time, she left me completely bewildered and i learnt to embrace the mystery of not knowing—letting go of the need to know—allowing myself to feel my way through life once again,’ clara said to maeve. this is the story of clara, a beautiful young irish girl, and her quest for what lies beneath the veil. 
they see in her a gift but must let her make her own voyage of discovery. as clara seeks her freedom, she struggles to find the divine light to transform herself. haunted by the dark secrets of her past: a deadly betrayal, unspoken and unspeakable, she is too scared to reveal her truth, knowing she will be further condemned and punished by her brother or father colin stanley or padraig mcdermott. 
her silence a betrayal of her soul. she waits in the nothingness, scared, she too, will become a fallen woman of the magdalene laundry. locked away. as she listens through the silence that surrounds her, the blood-stained truth engulfs her and her family. she must symbolically cleanse herself of her sins while the endless penance to god continues through abuse, humiliation and beatings. 
on her journey she is reunited with her aunt maeve, a wise woman who teaches her the gypsy ways and how to dance with the truths of the world. guided by maeve, clara begins a spiritual odyssey into realms of light and shadow, toward a final communion that will awaken or destroy her. will she rise from the darkness of the past and be free from the indoctrination of the remote irish catholic village? 
this tale, told with heart, speaks to the soul in each of us, delivering moments of illumination, a potent mix of divine feminine and masculine history, which will inspire you to remember who you are. ultimately, beneath the veil is a story about being able to forgive our past and trust in our becoming.

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.
#metoo#muterkelly #survivor#wosdvamwalk2019 #wosest2014 #velvetglovemedia #ce2

text:
this is why we must continue to fight for justice. cyntoia brown, a victim of child sex trafficking and rape, was granted clemency by tennessee governor, bill haslam. brown was previously sentenced to life in prison for shooting and killing 43-year-old armed child predator johnny allen, who bought cyntonia for sex when she was just 16 years old.

at the time cyntoia was living with a 24-year old pimp who went by the name "kut throat," who forced her into prostitution and raped her repeatedly. "the first time he did something to me is when he choked me and i passed out," brown recounts of her alleged pimp in the documentary. "i made him money...he wasn't going to let me go nowhere. he told me he'd kill me." cyntoia said she was scared for her life by allen's behavior, and took money after killing him for fear of returning empty handed to her pimp. despite clearly being the victim of child sex trafficking, cyntoia was tried as an adult and convicted of murder and robbery, and sentenced to life in prison.

if you look at cyntoia's original transcripts, they are peppered with the phrase "teen prostitute." but there is no such thing as a teen prostitute. a teen is a trafficking victim being manipulated and exploited by an adult.

despite national protest, in december, tennessee’s supreme court ruled that cyntoia must remain in prison for at least 51 years before she was eligible for release. a lawsuit was filed on her behalf arguing that mandatory life sentences without parole for juveniles was unconstitutional. the court rejected that contention, leading the women’s march to announce nationwide protests for brown and other sex-trafficking victims on jan. 19.
our voices have been heard. 
a survivor will be set free this year.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

text:
i finished two books last night and somehow all of the three books i have read this year have sexual assault as a main theme. 
and my first book that was entirely queer centric hysterical, was a difficult read for that reason. as much as i love gathering the stories of other queer people to hold in my heart, it gets exhausting to not only read about all of these traumatic things, but then later have to translate and condense all of that knowledge into an all too short 1000 word article.

it can feel like a betrayal to the memory of the people i write about to leave something out, but the cutting room floor is always full, and i just hope i have made the right choices. no matter what though, each story leaves me with something, a glimmer of hope, a fun story to share, a new admiration or hatred for a person. but i have a feeling this one will leave me with a small tear. 
so while i am happy to learn i am also hoping the next book i pick up will be more healing.

text:
to say that i am disgusted after watching ‘surviving r. kelly’ is an understatement and if the myriad of disturbing comments in the comments section of any article about the lifetime documentary series are any indication as to the mental and emotional state of the black community at large, r. kelly may never face justice, at least not by the u.s. justice system.

though not confined to the same prison as r. kelly’s victims and survivors, many black men and women are just as brainwashed by his manipulative mania let alone distracted by his musical talent. after sitting through and watching almost six hours of interviews, if we were to replay his music (i don’t recommend it) and listen intently with discerning ears, we’d all realize that we have been listening to explicit stories of sexual abuse and aggression all along.

yet, today in 2019, in response to the eyewitness stories of sexually abused black girls and black women in high definition, other black girls, black men, and black women say, “it doesn’t add up”. to whom i ask, what is there to add up? did we watch the same episodes? the research has already been done for us.

still, others have said “who am i to judge?”, which, to me, is a complete copout. the entire conversation from #blacklivesmatter to #metoo to #muterkelly is not about judging anyone but raising the level of national consciousness and holding perpetrators of crimes accountable for their actions.

as a black man, i am appalled that any man could defend or support the actions of r. kelly whether directly or indirectly. the adult complicity in this entire sex cult spans decades. truth be told, we all need healing because many of us have never learned what love is and what love is not, and to that end, we do not love ourselves.

i truly hope that at least one person that was asleep before is now awake. i’ve muted r. kelly years ago and will continue to do so.

#muterkelly #metoo #blacklivesmatter #blackgirlsmatter #blackwomenmatter #blackwriters #blackbloggers #blackmen #blackwomen #blackpeople #blackculture #blackchurches #blackcommunity #seesomethingsaysomething #endsexualviolence #endsextrafficking #letthehealingbegin #arebelwithapen

text:
elena sofia ricci: «io, violentata a dodici anni da un amico di famiglia»

ora che mia mamma è venuta a mancare posso parlare con libertà - ha detto - a 12 anni sono stata abusata. non l’ho mai dichiarato prima perché purtroppo è stata mia madre a consegnarmi, inconsapevolmente, nelle mani del mio carnefice, mandandomi in vacanza con un amico di famiglia». parole di elena sofia ricci, una delle attrici più amate del cinema e della tv italiana, che ha svelato un particolare terribile del suo passato in un’intervista al quotidiano libero. l’attrice, che ha 57 anni ha deciso di parlare del fatto dopo oltre 40 anni e dopo la morte della mamma. 
l’uomo, racconta elena, è stato poi arrestato perché lei stessa non era l’unica vittima e altre persone lo avevano denunciato. l’attrice è stata sempre in prima linea per il movimento #metoo e contro gli abusi ai danni delle donne nel mondo dello spettacolo: «nel mio caso si tratta di pedofilia, ma un abuso resta un abuso - ha aggiunto - nessun uomo ha il diritto di usare il proprio potere per abusare di una donna. quando una bambina che diventa ragazza è fragile, può arrivare a pensare di non meritarsi nulla e che deve vendersi. non è sempre facile dire no». elena sofia ricci tornerà presto a farci compagnia su raiuno con la nuova serie di che dio ci aiuti (in onda dal 10 gennaio). fonte: il messaggero

text_retweet:
#repost @ravanneviis

چندی پیش با فراگیر شدن هشتگ #metoo شبکه‌های اجتماعی پر شد از داستان قربانیان سوءاستفاده‌های جنسی. حرف زدن، آگاهی جامعه رو بالاتر میبره. فکر میکنم جا داره که کمی هم درباره‌ی سوءاستفاده‌ی عاطفی صحبت کنیم. مبحثی که جدیتش گاهی پشت شکل‌های دیگه‌ی آزار، گم میشه. 
سوءاستفاده‌ی عاطفی چیه؟ خیلی‌هامون میدونیم که ربطی به تحقیر کلامی شریک عاطفیمون داره. اما درست نمیدونیم که چه چیزهایی رو میشه زیر مجموعه‌ی چنین آزاری دونست، و اصلا آیا به اندازه‌ی بقیه‌ی انواع سوءاستفاده، جدی هست یا نه؟ کافیه در جایگاه گیرنده‌ی این سوءاستفاده‌ها باشیم تا ببینیم که به همون اندازه تخریب‌گر و ناراحت کننده هستند. در قانون انگلستان سوءاستفاده‌ی عاطفی حکم ۵ سال زندان رو داره. 
در‌ ادامه بیشتر در این باره صحبت میکنیم.

text: la peur de me faire harceler. 📍en tant qu’homme, je ne pourrai parler qu’avec le regard d’un homme. en tant que thérapeute, j’y vois quelques notions loin de tout expliquer. en tant qu’être humain, je parlerai avec mon cœur. 🌱 tout être est libre par essence de disposer de son corps comme il/elle le désire. en ce sens, ce n’est pas un devoir ni un idéal vers lequel tendre mais bien un postulat de base. quelle est alors notre part de responsabilité dans cette liberté ? aucune violence n’est justifiable. aucune. mais nous restons responsables, à ne pas confondre avec fautifs ou fautives, de ce que nous faisons de nos pensées, de nos croyances, de nos peurs, de nos émotions, de notre histoire, de notre vécu, de ce que nous disons, entendons, faisons et recevons. à 100%. 💡combien de fois la violence a été la réponse à la violence ? et combien de fois l’être humain a cherché à faire le bien avec autant de violence, de colère et de peur que ce qu’il cherche à changer ? nous le voyons dans les guerres, dans les luttes et combats du quotidien, familiaux, conjugaux, professionnels et sociaux : aucun conflit ne se résout en rentrant dans le conflit car tout conflit relationnel naît d’un conflit intra-personnel. autrement dit, seuls les conflits intérieurs créent des conflits à l’extérieur. je reçois beaucoup de femmes ayant vécu des expériences d’abus sexuel ou d’inceste - je n’utilise volontairement pas le mot victime - et tout notre travail est de reprendre le pouvoir de ce qu’elles font de ce qu’elles ont vécu. la première chose dont elles prennent conscience, c’est l’histoire qu’elles se racontent autour de cet événement douloureux. la deuxième, c’est qu’elles ont le pouvoir de ne pas s’identifier et se construire par rapport à cet événement. la troisième chose, c’est qu’elles ont le pouvoir de porter un autre regard sur cet événement et ce qu’elles vivent au présent. petit à petit, ces femmes passent de la peur de l’autre à l'amour de soi. dans une chambre noire, la plupart cherche à enlever le noir alors qu’il faudrait mettre de la lumière. pour retrouver confiance, sortons de la peur. 👻 #balancetapeur #metoo #noustoutes
name: Balance ta peur

text:
surviving r. kelly did exactly what it set out to do. for years, the women that have accused r. kelly have not been taken seriously. we've all heard the stories about the singer urinating on women and nothing has been made of that. there wasn't even much said about how he married #aaliyah when she was 15-years-old. now, people are finally taking action as a widespread attempt to cancel r. kelly from the industry has begun. many have started to speak out against the artist, claiming they had made mistakes by collaborating with him. despite kelly claiming that he will "expose" all of his accusers one by one, shark tank star daymond john has heard enough and he wants him gone.

so many women and men have spoken about how r. kelly has committed acts of sexual misconduct in the past and it was all documented in surviving r. kelly. the entertainment industry has been reacting to the lifetime docu-series along with the rest of the world and #sharktank's daymond john decided to voice his own opinion on twitter. "watching #survivingrkelly.i am so sick to my damn stomach!" wrote the fubu ceo. "hey @rkelly , please don’t take your life now that we all know how fucking disgusting you are. thats way too easy! make amends with the victims and the families, serve your time and then kill yourself while in jail." john didn't hold back at all and while many will be upset by his choice of words, he shares a sentiment that people will undoubtedly agree with. if he did the things he's being accused of, #rkelly should absolutely make amends with his victims and their families. ￼

text:
bohemian rhapsody won two “unexpected” awards at the golden globes, including best actor for rami malek and best motion picture (drama), catapulting the film into a legitimate oscars front-runner.
.
that “whoooooosh” noise you just heard was a can of gasoline being emptied onto the now-raging inferno that is the academy awards. it all leads to the question: are you ready for the most problematic oscars ever?
.
the film itself is a wash, a pandering and disrespectful portrait of a complicated man and artist that all but erases his queerness for the sake of placating four-quadrant crowds. but plenty of bad movies have won golden globes, and oscars, too. what is more troubling is the fact that the film arrived in today’s #metoo and #timesup climate – an era when power players and gatekeepers across the industry have pledged real change – courtesy (sort of) director bryan singer.
.
in december of 2017, singer was accused of sexual assault by cesar sanchez-guzman, citing an alleged 2003 incident when sanchez-guzman was 17. in 2014, former child actor michael egan claimed in a lawsuit that the director sexually assaulted him in 1999. egan later withdrew his suit, and singer has denied all the accusations.
.
a few days before sanchez-guzman filed a lawsuit against singer, the director was fired from bohemian rhapsody by 20th century fox, with the studio citing the “unexpected unavailability” of the filmmaker during production.
.
fox hired director dexter fletcher to complete filming, but singer retained his directing credit – even if his name was not uttered once at the golden globes. when asked backstage about singer, who did not attend sunday night’s gala, bohemian rhapsody producer graham king said, “that’s not something we should talk about tonight.”
.
so if not sunday night, then when? on the eve of the academy awards, perhaps, now that bohemian rhapsody is all but guaranteed a best-picture nomination? the answer, more likely, is never – especially if we’re trusting the academy awards to stand up where the golden globes fell down.
—
follow the link in our bio for barry hertz’s full story

text: over the last several days, many individuals have learned about the horrific acts of violence and abuse that myself and many other women suffered at the hands of r. kelly. while many in the public are just learning about the extent of r. kelly's abuse and coming to grips with his chronic repulsive behavior, the abuse is something his victims have had to live and cope with for many years. because robert kelly was and is such a well-known powerful figure, there are individuals and entities who continue to try and protect him by attacking and blaming his victims. they attack us. these r. kelly enablers are engaged in a campaign to defame and slander my name and to re-victimize me, as well as others, in an effort to protect r. kelly and minimize his detestable and abhorrent behavior. i refuse to be a victim again. in december of last year, i took the first step towards standing up to these bullies and r. kelly accomplices by issuing the above cease and desist letters to several individuals through my attorneys. i hope that blogs and gossip sties will not continue to aid and abet the vicious harassment and bullying of these r. kelly accomplices, and instead will stand with myself and the other victims who deserve your support. his time is up. #muterkelly #metoo #asantemcgee#survivingrkelly

text:
i’ve been to the #furkapass in switzerland and i have to say, the views driving up were beautiful💙

the picture is a throwback of a time in my life when i was in deep distress, being in a very abusive relationship with someone who made me feel less than nothing. 
it has been so hard for me to even look at the images from this trip, that it has taken me two years until today that i finally found an image of myself posing alone, strong and independent looking. reflecting who i truly am. except i was feeling so scared in this picture. i was scared all the time. 
one year after this picture was snapped, i left the person who mistreated me, and now i can look back at the pictures and think that all bad things will pass, just like the signage says furka’pass’- i have ‘passed’ those days. and i finally can see myself again. i am feeling like myself again.

i hope everyone, both male and female who are either in an abusive relationship or a survivor can find strenght to overcome it and leave the past behind. 💙
.
.
.
.
.
#picoftheday  #female #beautiful #suisse #happy #mountain #music #alps #swissalps #fashion #europe #zurich #skiing #landscapephotography #dark #sun #abusesurvivor #independentwoman #strongwomen #survivor #imasurvivor #switzerland #roadtrip #metoo

.
a shoutout to all the survivors out there. i will never be the same again, but i am healing my body and soul slowly slowly one step at a time..
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i’m going to try to be strong and watch the surviving r. kelly lifetime documentary tonight. i want to see first hand why the sudden outrage and hype. we have known for years about the accusations against r. kelly and his interest in young girls. now more comes out as many celebrities and others are outraged about the documentary.

why so much outrage now? where was all the outrage years ago when dave chappell and the boondocks were doing comedy skits about this? it wasn’t funny then and it isn’t funny now!

now there is also a muterkelly movement. this is a nationwide, grassroots movement to end the career of r&b singer and sexual abuser of young black women. i guess it’s never too late to pay attention and listen but why does it have to take so much? i can’t help but wonder, how many young girls and families could have been saved from this had more people took notice and paid attention earlier. this is the sad reality of the world we live in. 
this is why i do what i do, we have to start paying attention. we can’t remain silent. so many are counting on us to speak up and so many more can find their voice, courage, and get help if we just listen and be supportive.

#sexyaftersexualassault #muterkelly #timesup #metoo #youarenotalone #enoughisenough #itcouldbeyourdaughter #ibelieveyou #nomorevictimblaming #alllivesmatter #bystanderintervention #supporteachother #payattention #nevergiveup #endviolenceagainstwomen  #lovenothate❤️ #endrapeculture #listen

text: this is petty at its finest, mostly everyone is aware that “bohemian rhapsody” was directed by bryan singer who’s best known for directing “the usual suspects” and 4 of the main 6 “x-men” films. singer was fired from bohemian with 3 weeks left of shooting due to being a backstage head constantly getting into epic disagreements with rami malek. even going as far as throwing equipments around. dexter fletcher ( director of the upcoming elton john biopic “rocketman”) came on board to finish the 3 weeks left of shooting along with doing post production work. yesterday night after neither rami or producer graham king thanked him when bohemian won 2 of the biggest awards of the night, singer took it upon himself to thank the hollywood foreign press on a instagram post for the honors bestowed on his film but posting a behind the scenes picture with him directing a scene. the biggest take away from the picture is that he made sure the visible sign of “director” on his chair was visible. now besides these behind the scenes incidents singer who is openly bisexual  is known for being a sexual predator and known rapist having had kids ranging from ages 14-17 accused him of sexual assault over the last 20 years. now i still love bohemian and i am super happy about its success it’s a tad baffling and funny that a awards show that praises itself for standing up against spacey and weinstein gave the biggest award of the night to a film that is directed by a guy that is just as horrible a human being as kevin spacey.#bohemianrhapsody#queen#freddiemercury#ramimalek#goldenglobes#bryansinger#xmen#x2xmenunited#theusualsuspects#xmendaysoffuturepast#xmenapocalypse#aptpupil#supermamreturns#valkyrie#kevinspacey#harveyweinstein#petty#metoo#gay#bisexual#rapist#radiogaga#wewillrockyou#wearethechampions#liveaid1985

text:
again needed an over 40 guinea pig for my book, so i’m it again! almost 50 i will have you know! 😉anyway here is the quote i want to post to encourage the new singers trying to “find their voice” and if i could have a life, without the subsequent corruption that historically can accompany these levels of success and is finally starting to change, thank god, where one can just sing and sing, and write like elvis did that i always imagine that would be the life! no grueling tours scheduled is part of the imagined peace here for me! anyway, here is the heart i feel you need to break personal and professional barriers to true success as a singer and a beautiful way to be: “i learned very early in life that: ‘without a song, the day would never end; without a friend, a man ain't got a friend; without a song, the road would never bend- without a song’ so i keep singing a song.” elvis’ quote and acceptance speech in 1970. “keep singing and don’t let anyone steal your voice!” my quote, evita, 2019! ✌️ i learned very early in life that: "without a song, the day would never end; without a friend, a man ain't got a friend; without a song, the road would never bend- without a song" so i keep singing a song.  https://www.instagram.com/p/bkkmvbvha8v/?utm_source=ig_share_sheet&igshid=186zw394kx0l0

“the loss of a sense of dignity and respect in the macho breeds a false machismo which leads him to put down women and even brutalize them. coexisting with his sexist behavior is a love for the mother which takes precedence over that of all others. devoted son, macho pig. to wash down the shane if his acts, of his very being, and to handle the brute in the mirror, he takes to the bottle, the snort, the needle, and the fist. 
though we ‘understand’ the root causes of male hatred and fear, and the subsequent wounding of women, we do not excuse, we do not condone, and we will no longer put up with it. from the men of our race, we demand the admission/disclosure/testimony that they wound us, violate us, are afraid of us and our power. we need them to dat they will begin to eliminate their hurtful put-down ways. but more than the words, we demand acts. we say to them: we will develop equal power with you and those who have shamed us.” ~gloria anzaldúa

#librosrecomendados : tsunami (#sextopiso ) ♡ #escritoras de distintas generaciones exploran las distintas facetas del ser #mujer : hablar sobre nuestra representación (o la falta de ella), las etiquetas que nos son impuestas que nos violentan tanto histórica como culturalmente y como abordamos nuestra resistencia. 
respecto a la #antología escribe marina cruz m: tsunami es un libro de "acompañamiento" mientras enfrentamos la realidad de nuestra "condición". por un lado está el derrumbe de la idea romántica de la maternidad de una forma brutal gracias a daniela rea. cristina rivera garza explica qué se hace cuando te mandan a callar. margo glantz  busca el origen de la violencia que, a su vez, nos lleva a movimientos como #metoo
el libro es tan diverso y hermoso que incluye poesía de verónica gerber bicecci y jimena gonzález, a quien para concluir cito:
"alzo la voz para no negarnos,
porque tenemos nombre
y no dejaremos que lo olviden". #escritorasmexicanas  #amoleer #somoslectores #mujerestrabajando #feminismo #bookstagram

@kyliejenner, can you imagine taking a stroll outside your home, only to be whisked away forcibly to marry someone? it's not unheard of in kyrgyzstan. although it's illegal, the practice of bride kidnapping is an ongoing kyrgyz "tradition". consequences for these women leaving these marriages include rape, shunning and even attempted suicide. but one kyrgyz woman who escaped bride kidnapping, gazbubu babaiarova, is battling this practice with education and by debunking the myth that this is a legitimate tradition. read more about this #metoo movement and others from around the world by going to the link in our bio.
.
.

text:
today on the blog... as i watched i was astonished at the number of people who were involved indirectly or passively enabled his predatory behavior. grown adults recruiting younger girls for him at the mall, concerts, etc., grown adults who a marriage license so he could marry a 15 year old girl, grown adults who were arranging flights, transportation, and hotel stays to house young girls for this sexual deviant….sighs… out of all of these people, not one adult had the moral fiber or basic human decency to say something? did no one care about these girls?
i don’t think it was something i thought about previously. i’d been so focused on r. kelly as a predator i failed to realize as a celebrity, he needed assistance to continuously do this for over 20 years. as i watched in horror at these adults attempting to purge their guilt by sharing their stories i became so angry. they knew what was happening and said nothing because of a check. it made me want to scream out in frustration and cry tears of absolute weariness. this man had an entire team of people helping him rape and abuse women for over 2 decades! i feel like a broken record…does anyone care enough about black girls?

text:
así de feliz salio el actor kevin spacey después de su comparecencia ante un juez de distrito de la exclusiva localidad de nantucket (massachusetts) para que se le leyeran los cargos de presunto asalto sexual a un joven de 18 años en julio de 2016, donde no pronunció ni una sola palabra durante la vista de cerca de 11 minutos.

la vista de nantucket es la primera que puede significar cargos criminales contra el actor de 59 años, que enfrenta otras investigaciones y más de 30 denuncias por supuesto asalto sexual en los ángeles e inglaterra. el juez fijó una fecha para una nueva vista el próximo lunes 4 de marzo, vista en la que spacey estará exento de comparecer, saliendo así libre bajo fianza.

text:
this is the reason why people are so afraid to say no. this leads them to become so unhappy/scared to continue the relationship or conversation. but when they say no, they’re attacked. the next time someone says ‘girls are so confusing’ and are giving mixed signals maybe this is the reason why. we’re just contemplating which situation is going to be the better one for us, which one isn’t going to get us killed. if a guy says ‘if she don’t want to she will just say no’ maybe not. maybe she’s too scared. no means no, but so does flinching, silence, being unconscious. and if someone says ‘why don’t girls just say no if they don’t want to it’s not that hard’, women are scared men will kill them and men are scared women will laugh at them. ‘misandry irritates and misogyny kills’. it’s so terrifying that we have come into a world where we need a #timesup to tell us we need to stop sexual harassment and rape. we need a #metoo for survivors to come out because the environment at home/in society is too frightening and filled with support for the predator and questioning and victim blaming for the survivor. this needs to change, enough is enough.

text: let that sink in. i am so grateful my experiences have not hindered my life so much that i cannot accept love but god knows i cringe at aggression i get nervous around a group of men i can’t stand older men telling me i’m attractive. i have a fear of being kidnapped so bad bc of feeling like i couldn’t say no without choked or told i couldn’t be anything without anyone physical and verbal abuse. i think back on situations daily thinking wow at 18 and 19 you shouldn’t of been looking at my 13 year old body or trying to kiss me or have me touch them... being raped in my older years getting told “ we grown “ at 16 and 17 when we weren’t anything you were but i was a child and shouldn’t of been pressured . i thought sex for a long time was the only way anyone would look at me bc that’s the only way anyone seemed to look at me since i was 6 years old ...to watch that... i died all over again i still am not finished because it’s hard to get through. do not watch this and joke it’s not funny. maybe it’s funny to you because you are one in the same ... maybe bc you are coping but realize it’s not funny.

text:
i'm about to get personal now so if you're not interested, just hit like on the pretty images and just scroll on by. there is a deeper reason i take pictures beyond my love for "pretty" things. truth is i never felt pretty growing up. looking back, i can see now that i really was a cutie. i just didn't have the eyes i have today. 
this set of pictures (thanks to my baby girl for being my muse)  beautifully explains who i was then. "beautifully silenced" 
just a pretty little girl without a voice surrounded by obstacles that caged me in. the things that were happening to me at the hands of people i should have been able to trust stole my innocence & my life for many years. shame was hidden behind an unending quest to be perfect on the outside while i remained horribly sad inside. i became a cynical, opinionated, competitive, over-achiever with lots of relational conflict on a continual quest for something or someone to make me feel like i had a purpose. 
in school i was bullied because of what i looked like & as i matured i lashed back or ran away.i tried to be what the world wanted. they still didn't want me..and some still don't. 
today i realize that my story is just one of millions that  can say #metoo. we know darkness but can can learn to live in light. i'm proof. i know what it's like to not have 1 person get it. unless you have actually experienced sexual abuse, you truly don't know what it does to your mind. but please believe me when i say, you can live a normal life. you can heal. today i do know who i am. yes, it's work. everyday. good days or bad i know my struggles will pass. i once had a therapist tell me i was like a little bird with a broken wing and it would always be that way. she was so wrong. so much of me has been restored. when i hit my final bottom, & in my hopelessness i chose to look up. the creator of the universe i hadn't previously really knew i got to know and learned that he says i'm worthy. he says i'm loved. he said i'm his. the love of jesus changed my life for good. he has given me gifts. gifts like this i get to share with you all today.  #nevergiveup and thank you to those who choose to read.
name: 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐥🦋Dream2Be Image Photo

text:
very true. 
from being raped at 14 and 16 i learned a lot from that time in my life. 
being diagnosed with crohn's at 18 on july 2, 2008 and almost dying in october 2009 from crohn's. 
that taught me more about myself. 
i was 80 lbs and in the hospital for 3 weeks. major surgery. away from my parents and my daughter. 
i didn't know if i would make it home to my baby girl.
hard things in life teach you things and you realize that down the road. 
you are strong, and you grow from every thing that happens. 
#strength #quotes #raped #crohns #lessonslearned #crohnsdisease #mother #life #metoo

text: but god. 🙌🏾 i can remember doing my psychology paper on her years ago. i was so heartbroken. i couldn’t understand why a judge would basically take away her life due to what a grown man has done. should she have gotten off scott free? no. but she was a child born into the worst possible situation and to the worst possible people. rehabilitation was necessary. she had obvious mental and developmental issues that led her to be pulled into sex trafficking and eventually committing murder. the odds were stacked against her from birth. there was no doubt in my mind those charges would have been a lot different if the color of her skin was different. but i digress. she had no one to protect her and shield her from grown ass men who prey on lost little girls. the only difference between her and r kelly’s victims is that she took matters into her own hands. these are little girls. no one else will protect little brown girls so we have to commit to protecting them at all costs. as a sexual assault survivor i know exactly how they got into the situations they were in. i know the feeling of not being able to say “no”. i know the feeling of being manipulated so bad that you have no clue who you are anymore. it’s not hard for me to understand their stories. none of these are “fast” girls. they’re victims. i’m praising god today that she is a survivor and she will get a second chance to live her life and start over with what she knows now. #browngirlslivesmatter #cyntoiabrown  #protectourgirls  #muterkelly  #survivor  #metoo

text: sending this rose to survivors specifically the black women & girls who told their stories on #survivingrkelly ~ #beliveblackwomen #blackgirlslivesmatter the #metoo movement was started by @taranajaneen and focused on uplifting black women and girls who have experienced sexual violence. she put out a live on the documentary and as a survivor and someone who has focused on trauma healing myself i felt it was important to witness. while i don’t have a tv i was able to watch the documentary yesterday (major trigger warning and please take care survivors). the documentary centered the survivors including his ex-wife and the ways in which young girls were manipulated, gaslighted, abused, assaulted, separated from family and loved ones by a man @rkelly who is enabled by yes men, @rcarecords, and legal shelters of ndas, and enabled by people who simply do not value black women and girls✨ in the midst of all this, the bravery of the survivors who showed up to to help others .... you matter, your story matters and most of all your joy, healing and processing of your trauma matters.

text:
with all of the controversy that is going on with #survivingrkelly and all of us that have been through abuse by the hands of a man... i want to make sure to make this statement. 
dear black man, 
we love u. we will not let the actions of one man make us look at u any different. we appreciate u. we have your back. we know that us as queens need our kings to be a powerful force in this cruel world of hate. we will continue to fight by your side and unite our kingdoms. through this journey there will be sacrifices, there will be traders. there will be some whom don't believe in the love and respect that we have for one another. those people we must let go. r. kelly is one of those. he didn't respect us queens. he believes in only self and not unity. as hard as it is, we must sacrafice him and let him go. that is no way a reflection on u, black man. we love u. we respect u. we appreciate u and we cherish u. 
with love, 
black women

text:
issa bout time!!! #cyntoiabrown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the #tennessee governor's office.
____________
the campaign for cyntoia brown's clemency brown will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. #billhaslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.
___________
"cyntoia brown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope."
___________
brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a number of  celebrities like #amyschumer, #amandaseales, #kimkardashian,actress #ashleyjudd were among the many who called for brown's #clemency.
____________

text:
here are some stats about sexual assault on college campuses. this convo is important to have but what about everything that goes on before college? high school, middle school? we have to address the different cultures and attitudes that have contributed to this issue from the very beginning. we can’t limit this conversation to just higher education/college campuses. sexist dress codes are implemented since middle school, the phrase "boys will be boys" is used throughout elementary, middle school, and high school
~
in a given school year, an estimated 58% of 7th - 12th graders experience some form of sexual violence, especially sexual harassment. a 2011 study published by @aauwnational investigated sexual violence that occurs in middle/high school & found that in an academic year, 13% of girls reported that they had been inappropriately touched in an “unwelcome sexual way," in this same year, 4% reported being forced to perform a sexual act, & 1 in 20 girls who had been sexually harassed transferred to a different school in hopes of avoiding the torment. we have to protect our young students!
.
.
.
stat credits: @motherjonesmag @aauwnational 
#metoo #believesurvivors #twbwomensmarch #twbforsurvivors #womenswave #truthtopower

text:
[3/5] for years, when i would look at old photographs of myself i would be so confused as to why i wasn’t smiling in any of them. now i know why. i was bullied throughout middle school and high school which made my inner turmoil grow even more, and as if things couldn't get worse i was date-raped at 15. being raped added a layer to the emotional damage that was already a fixture inside of my soul, but this time i felt i had to tell someone because the stakes were too high. i decided to open up to my mom about what had happened and even revealed that my uncle had molested me, i have made peace with the fact that my mother’s response to my truth was less than ideal. as is common with many survivors of sexual abuse, the onus is always on us, the victims, to explain what we “did” to contribute to the assault taking place regardless of how old we are. as a result of the lack of validation, i internalized messages of self-blame and self-hatred. after that attempt, i never felt comfortable speaking about it again. the way i coped with my silence was by partying on weekends and using drugs, i kept the company of men who were destructive and hung out with the wrong crowd. my parents would try to get a hold of me when i was out but i refused to come home, i wanted to run away and i didn’t want to live in my body anymore. popping ecstasy seemed so much easier than having to bear the burden of so much trauma, so i would use it to escape the realities of my life. one of the silver linings in my childhood was my relationship with my sister, ruchika (pictured here). the only photographs i have of myself in my early days where i am smiling are when i am with her. i went into mama bear mode at young age and i think it’s because deep down i didn’t want the same thing that had happened to me to happen to her. despite all the pain and the heartache that i experienced so young, there was a desire to protect and shelter others, which has pushed me to live to tell my story.
✍🏼 @pri_pards

r. kelly plans to expose his accusers with new website called “surviving lies” - blogged by @msjennyb
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
days after the final episodes of the disturbing six-part docuseries, “surviving r. kelly,” which chronicled years of sexual, mental and emotional abuse at the hands of the controversial superstar, the self-proclaimed pied piper of r&b is preparing to have the last word with an exposé of his own. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
according to tmz, kelly has vowed to expose his accusers for what he claims to be blatant lies on the lifetime docu-series, and sources say he’s checking off his list one by one. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in fact, according to the publication, kelly and his camp are preparing to launch a new website called “http://survivinglies.com” to turn the tables on those who’ve exposed him. but until then, the singer’s team has created a new facebook page dedicated to clearing kelly’s name. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
apparently, kelly’s first target is asante mcgee, who claimed to be one of the singer’s “sex slaves.” in a video linked to the singer’s new page, asante’s daughter apparently refutes her mother’s claims of sexual abuse in a leaked conversation with her boyfriend, allegedly claiming asante often bragged about the lavish life she lived with him. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in addition to the video, the new page also details asante’s criminal history and alleges that she’s working with joycelyn savage’s father to get money out of the singer. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
however, the information on the new page has yet to be verified.

⠀
📌8mm. приложение для съемки видео с ретро эффектами.
⠀
📌videoleap. приложение по обработке видео (склейки, наложение музыки и и.д.)
⠀
📌unfold. рамки для видео и фото.
⠀
📌plot. фото делаются сразу в приложении и на них автоматически накладывается фильтр и рамка поллароид.
⠀
📌kuni cam (как бы странно это ни звучало) обработка фото с возможностью добавления потёртостей и засветов.

i remember seeing him about 7 years back in chicago at a restaurant.. he was sitting with two young black girls.. thinking back now it probably was two of his victims.  my mind is just blown and i pray that law enforcement does something soon about this. he has ruined so many young lives already.

text: posting for the people who have not yet found their voice. all this talking and joking about sexual abuse, because of the man i refuse to name, is a trigger for survivors of such ordeals. 1 in 9 girls and 1 in 53 boys (probably more but boys are less likely to report their sexual abuse) have been sexually abused by the age of 18. think about it. if there are 18 girls in your child’s class room at least 2 of them have been sexually abused. as a survivor of sexual abuse myself, just scrolling threw all my social media posts and seeing everyone talk about sexual abuse or making memes or joking about it is a trigger for me. i had nightmares last night recounting my own sexual abuse. it didn’t feel like it was going to trigger me, but the brain does fucked up stuff when you are sleeping. check in on your friends and just make sure they know they’re loved and supported if need be. and if anyone ever ever ever needs someone to confide in or vent to. i got you. message me and your secrets will always be safe with me. i’ll show you screen recordings of me deleting whatever you want or whatever. #metoo #survivor #neveravictim #fuckmyabusers

text:
r. kelly is reportedly creating a website to expose all of his accusers. 
the r. kelly story just keeps on getting more and more complicated. this weekend, twitter absolutely blew up after each episode of surviving r. kelly aired. the docu-series focuses on the years of abuse that the singer has been accused of handing out. in each episode, interviews with his accusers are shown and the artist is obviously not pleased with the outcome. many are calling for him to be blacklisted from the industry, claiming that enough is finally enough. others are waiting for kellz to explain himself. those of you that are putting a pause on cancelling him right away will be interested in learning that r. kelly is reportedly planning to go down his list of accusers one by one, exposing them all as liars. 
according to tmz, r. kelly will soon be going live with a website called survivinglies.com. as of now, a facebook page exists under the same name and it seems as though the singer will be going after asante mcgee first. the publication notes that r. kelly will go down his list of accusers one by one in an attempt to prove that they are all lying about him. 
people close to the artist are stating that he will soon be launching the website, which will reveal his accusers’ “true motivations.” with dozens of women speaking out against the singer, he likely has his work cut out for him with this. what do you guys think? get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #muterkelly #metoo #lifetime #lifetimetv #trappedinthecloset #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #survivinglies

text:
when it comes to buying a home, i prefer the first option. buy something small, simple and cheap. it's better to pay for a place that has all utilities worked into the hoa. the hoa can go up or down depending on the board members greed.

most old people live in apartments until they reach the senior home, so avoid the massive house, think like you're 60. canadians buy cheap apartments and trailer homes in fla, so they retire much more than americans, cuz americans have huge mortgages.

if you want to buy with mortgage, buy something under 150k new or under 100k auction/foreclosed. hopefully you have a trade that can go anywhere so you can move where homes are cheap. if you're in ny or cali, you're screwed.

there are two type of people buying homes, dumb asses and wise asses.

when a dumb ass says i'm going to spend 500k on a home that means he'll search for a home within the 250k-500k and buy it.

when a wise person says i'm going to spend 500k on a home,  that means he will search for a home within 100-250k range and buy it cash.

with the remaining 250k he can setup a trust that pays all the bills automatically out of the remainder.

he can also do what smart ball players do (the ones you don't hear about). purchase the home 250k with your 500k budget in mind. put 100k into home repair account. pay 50k on taxes up front and another 50k on utilities/insurance upfront.

very few people do this option but this is how you buy with security and peace of mind. the same rule applies to a person buying a 50k studio. if your budget is 100k for a studio,  buy a foreclosure and have some friends in construction and remodeling do the fix up for about 25k.

with the remainder, put 15k on taxes and 10k on utilities/insurance. if your taxes are 1000 a year on a 50k studio. you paid 15 years up front assuming the price stays the same (which it won't). therefore if anything happens, whether you end up in a coma, injured, go to prison or whatever, you have a home with bills and taxes paid for next 20-30 years.

you can use the extra income to go back to school and get another trade to be able to make your own home remodels or save up for another cheap place you can rent out.

text:

.
.
i’ve doubted my memories and perception most of my life. it was safer. but then i see that young teenage girl, and all she wasn’t saying but was secretly desperate to. .
.
.
if i can only give one permission slip to one person the rest of my life, it’ll be permission to tell the truth about your story. healing and truth are so intricately connected, and i want so much for you to heal. .
.
.
don’t give up, open up. .
.

text:
i’m willing to be controversial. ⁣
⁣
i’m also willing to be wrong. ⁣
⁣
i help burnt-out women because i was a burnt-out woman. i was running on empty, hustling, working, giving so much to others and not replenishing my own cup. ⁣
⁣
burn out looked like:⁣
⁣
severe fatigue where no amount of coffee could help. ⁣
crying before going into work because i had nothing in me.⁣
painful periods that made me vomit.⁣
a messy home because i would give and do so much for others i didn’t even have the energy to support myself. ⁣
low sex drive.⁣
bloating. ⁣
crippling anxiety.⁣
depression where i couldn’t see myself as worthy because everyone and everything else took precedent. ⁣
⁣
in the thick of #timesup #metoo and more, it’s imperative that women learn how to take care of themselves so we can continue to show up everyday and dismantle toxic masculinity. ⁣
⁣
and it starts with you. ⁣
how you talk to yourself.⁣
how you wake up in the morning.⁣
how you move about your day. ⁣
⁣
it starts in your kitchen.⁣
your yoga class.⁣
your bath. ⁣
⁣
consider ayurveda as part of your tool bag. something you can return to over and over no matter how you’re feeling. ⁣
⁣
ayurveda is a life-long practice and i’m in it for longevity, to avoid burn-out and to know how to navigate it if it does happen again. ⁣
⁣
this wisdom is within me and it’s within you, too. sometimes we just need someone to hold the mirror. ⁣
⁣
send me a message if this speaks to you and we can work together to support you during and after burn-out. ⁣
⁣
sending you all so much love. xo

text: “surviving r kelly” the docuseries was compelling on so many levels. i commend dream hampton on bringing together individuals - entertainment industry insiders, family, and victims. i’m certain this was no easy task as many people don’t chose to speak on this topic. i myself struggled in my decision on whether or not i should post about this for several reasons. i am among many who continued to mute my protest of r kelly’s alleged behavior by purchasing his music and listening to it on the radio and at events. also this a touchy, personal conversation for many of us. so the decision to address this on a public platform came after a bit of internal deliberation and conversations with several friends. the docuseries clearly states at its start that r kelly was once a victim himself. for that, i feel sad for the little boy who never got help for the abuse and neglect he suffered at the hands of family and other adults in his life. but this does not negate his poor choices to not deal with his own issues, rather turn the abuse on innocent people. to hear the depth of of r kelly’s warped ideas of relationships, his misuse of his platform, and his total abuse of power through his gift and blessings is sickening. i am not the judge nor jury of his career or ultimate fate in life. i do truly hope that through this spotlight, through the pain that we hear from victims, that the injustice that r kelly has been allowed to commit, i pray it all comes to an end. we have to hold ourselves accountable for how we exalt individuals because of their talents, money, or power. wrong is wrong. let’s not ignore what is right before our eyes. #muterkelly

text:
four years after graduating college... .
•
i was reporting live in front of the white house for nbc. if i looked scared shitless, i was. .
•
this was the biggest moment in my young tv journalist career to date. .
•
i had just turned 25. it was the white house. my dress was from marshall’s. i may have overdrafted to even buy it. .
•
if i looked scared shitless, i was for another reason too. .
•
moments before this picture was taken, a man of great power and authority cornered me in the hallway outside the room i was about to go live in. 
he brushed up against my leg. i could smell his stale breath against my cheek as he called me “doll” and offered to “help” me. .
•
it would be the first of countless times i was sexually harassed in this industry. .
•
i tell you the former because never be surprised at how quickly your dreams and goals manifest when you’re clear and work damn hard. .
•
i share with you the later to never lose hope that, as bob dylan says, the times. they are a changing. .
•
share this with any young woman so she sees we’ve been fighting to make sure she never even *knew there was a glass ceiling. .
•
#metoo #believewomen #bossify

・・・
take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasn’t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesn’t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i don’t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, i’m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every #survivor know, that “everyone of us is worthy” and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo

text:
this is the year that i launch my non-profit i am still looking for board members who are really dedicated to the cause of helping black and brown girls and women who are victims of sexual abuse and trafficking in inner city neighborhoods... my mission is focused on rescue and reintroduction/rehabilitation into a stable life. by now many of you have seen surviving r. kelly and know the impact it can have not only on the victims but their families. i know we all have been, or know someone who has fallen victim to predatory behavior... especially in our own community. i've been working toward this for about the last 2 years and starting to round things out. even if you're not interested... i'm asking that you share my post so that it gets into the hands of someone truly dedicated to helping this cause.

text:
hey klubbers! this weekend i took the time out to watch the 6 part documentary on surviving r.kelly! as i watched with the million of viewers i watched not subconsciously knowing the history and constant quiet reminders of jokes made through black culture.(boondocks episode). • 
as me and my friends watch this together we discussed very different but understanding view points on the subject. we acknowledge the abuse and victimization, the long history of sexual misconduct with minors that we’ve ignored as a collective. we talked about separating the monster from the music (if that’s possible and do we have to chose). it made a face our own traumatic experiences with older guys we’ve encountered during this life journey. if you can watch it. black women deserve to be believed, support and nurtured too! • 
hug on your daughter,
mother, sister, cousin and more. we are changing the narrative around the treatment of black women, motherhood, business and community now let’s continue the fight but without forgetting the victimization and molestation of our brown boys either. there are causes we can stop. •
#blackmomsbelike #survivingrkelly #sexual #metoo #blackwomen #community #philadelphia #blackmotherhood #saveourbabies #conversationstarters

text:
عکس اول: 
دیوار نوشته‌ای در سلیمانیه عراق، نوشته "عشق مرزی نداره" 😍🌈
اینجوریه که اگە اتباعش خارج از کشور ازدواج کنند، بیان توی اقلیم کردستان از شرایط برابر با بقیه برخوردارن، اما این کشور چون جزو عراقه نمیتونن خودشون قانون ازدواج lgbt+ها رو تصویب کنن پس مجبورن خارج ازدواج کنند.
اما مثلا حزب ه د پ توی کردستان ترکیه حامی lgbt+ها هست و حامی اینە ک توی ترکیه ازدواجشون رو رسمی کنە.
.عکس دوم: ‏برافراشته شدن پرچم lgbt+ در رقه از سوى گروهى متشكل از شبه نظاميان lgbt+ كه همراه با كردها به مصاف داعش در سوريه رفته اند😍🤘
.
حزب ه د پ الان به شدت ضعیف شده
سران حزب در زندان هستند و دیگه اون وضعیت ۳سال پیش در فضای سیاسی ترکیه از بین رفته است و ما شاهد صف آرایی سیاسی جدیدی در ترکیه هستیم با محوریت اسلامگرایی و ترک بودن و ملی گرایی و البته دگرجنسگرامحوری.

text:
stop the silence!! after an amazing weekend with fellow men of achievement in tampa florida for kappa alpha psi fraternity,  inc. 14th annual founders day.  i found myself up late sunday evening watching hours of "surviving r. kelly" on lifetime.  words cannot begin 2 describe my disappointment in us as a society for decades of abuse, sexual assault,  manipulation,  and degradation of young teenage girls. ☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆
how and why has this illegal activity been allowed 2 go on for so long?  the moral compass of our country is really at an all time low.  the docuseries featured survivors of r. kelly's cult, former staff, friends and family of the victims.  i applaud their bravery for speaking out and not remaining silent.  thank you 2 tom joyner, chance the rapper, and john legend for taking a conscious stand against r. kelly.  we need more men in this movement 2 truly move the needle in the right direction.  especially since most of the perpetrators of rape and sexual assault are males.  as a gender we as males are a big part of the problem.  and now it's time 2 be a bigger part of the solution. ☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆
everyone has a voice and should use it for the betterment of us all. "silence is the antithesis of effectiveness." dont just sit idly by and allow this history of violence 2 continue.  2 many people have been adversely affected and so many suffer in silence. future generations need you 2 shield them from abuse. hidden and unspoken cycles of sexual violence is a problem. which is why i've served as an advocate for over 2 decades. hopefully you will use your platform and stand with me. 💫
☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆
#stoptheviolence #breakthecycle #nomoresilence #startbybelieving #metoo #muterkelly #lifetime #pbcvictimservices #nancyjcottermancenter #fcasv #fcadv #tomjoyner #chancetherapper #johnlegend #kappaalphapsi #survivingrkelly #chicagopd #standup

text:
survivors of violence (interpersonal, systemic) i believe you, i see you. your story is valid, your life is beautiful.
.
.
femmes and non binary folks of color- your bodies & lives are beautiful, may those who hurt you fall, may they repent.
.
all oppressed beings- what binds us is our struggle for recognition & healing. i believe in our abilities to thrive.
.
in the past i’ve opened up donation based protection spells for survivors. i don’t really have the spoons for that at the moment... but i’ll let y’all know when i open up the spots again.
.
.
in the meantime- remember to take care of your heart. use lots of rosemary. put her fragrance on himalayan sea salt & throw it in the bath. warm your skin with her scent. hang her above your doorways. plant some marigolds, or poach some from a rich persons yard. dry them. put them in a bowl with lavender. carry rose quartz with you in your bag or pocket. burn cedar, bay leaves, douglas fir tips, mugwort or angelica root. write yourself a love letter.
.
#metoo #timesup #marigolds #flowermagic #plantwitch #greenwitch #protectionspell #witchcraft #herbalmagic #plantallies

normalmente nunca pido nada en mis redes sociales pero me parece un caso de extrema urgencia. si veis mis dos ultimas publicaciones de stories podéis comprobar como un partido español que se ha declarado totalmente conservador y que a mí personalmente su discurso me parece anti-feminismo. lleva varios días haciendo campaña en medios y en redes sociales en contra de las feministas, llamándonos feminazis y utilizando la imagen de otras mujeres para hacer creer que nos apoyan. de verdad, este partido cada vez capta más votantes en españa y me da pánico que muchas mujeres se sientan identificadas con su minista. tengo mucho miedo de que mujeres se sientan identificadas con su discurso. estoy aterrada de que un partido así exista en mi país y esté creciendo por momentos.
repito, podéis verlos en mis dos ultimas stories e informaros al respecto. no vamos a permitirlo. por todas. por las que ya no están y por las que tenemos el poder de cambiar el mundo.

promovamos el hashtag #voxnoesfeminista en las redes sociales.

#repost @kemaranight with @get_repost
・・・
‼️ #stepupaccountability2019 ‼️:
i'm not going to blame the youth. i shan't blame this on them, as we all know what it's like to be young, still having much to learn, but i do have a #straythought as all of these incidents pop up:

fvck age of consent laws because many states do have them too young, but in a culture where we celebrate a woman's maturity at ages such as 15 and 16 i.e. quinceaneras and sweet 16s, i find it interesting how we celebrate these parties from a lens of "coming into adulthood" yet are dumbfounded and consequently revoke titles of maturation if/when scenarios like this come up.

17 is still technically illegal in the eyes of federal law so drake fucked up, especially including the statements he made, but just the idea of why we still hold these big coming-of-age parties, calling them such and not simply just birthdays, yet revoke such adulthood in multiple instances is ironic in my eyes.

it seems we as a society groom children and teens in various ways for that treatment but then grown ass people take it upon themselves to take advantage of such and we are baffled ?????? it's our fault (society i.e. media outlets, influencers, loved ones, etc.) and the fault of the predator but i think, above all the former is most reprehensible because we skew lines, telling our youth they're grown in many ways (vs growing) and then snatch their autonomy and re-emphasize the young in "young adult" when it no longer suits our conveniences. i don't think i have to explain as much as y'all can just reflect on your own upbringings and digest this thought.

all-in-all, we too often place this burden upon the youth of america and question why such cases as these exist (and frequently more) whilst complacently / complicitly ignoring that we are the culprits of these behaviors whether it be due to our nonchalance over these behaviors, our silence, or even a misdirection of blame.

everybody treats accountability like it's this nasty, accusatory word - but it's not. it's the one thing that could set us free if we were only strong enough to lay down our egos and change some sh*t.

drop thoughts below.
let's talk.

text: no the face i want starting my week not the post i would like to make on a monday but it is part of my mission to share the dark side of being human, of being empath,  a healer and ptsd from a narcissist relationship • this. morning i woke up feeling happy and ready to tackle the day, got my girls ready for school, both made it on time and both were ready to have a great day. after dropping valerie i stopped to do some grocery shopping, while doing that i started feeling off, watching over my back, anxious to get out and wanting to cry. once i got to my car i realized the ptsd from that trauma was kicking in, i felt frustrated, tired of if, weak.  i cried. in an attempt to clear my head i grab my phone and star seeing his name on a person comment, then i look around and i see a car same brand as his, i checked myself to make sure this all was mine and not that i was picking up from someone else, also to make@sure no creepy energy was trying to sneak on me. you see even seeing that can trigger you, thats how intense the abuse was. i don’t like to see his, name, or anything related to reiki or his car brand. it triggers thoughts and then brings me back to all i went through, then i start asking myself how i let that happen. a full cycle until i am bring myself back and reach out to my support team. ptsd takes time to heal, the triggers show me how much healing i still need, how also how fast i bring myself back to the light when i have an “episode”. • all this because last night before going to bed i accidentally ended up reading someone else experience with a narc. • this shit is hard, but i also know this life lesson helps me heal and understand others better. give them tools based kn my own healing. fighting this battle help me guide other through theirs. • and for you asshole! i know you will read this, war is not over. i am a warrior of god....remember that.
name: Suhanna - The SpiritWalker LLC

text:
via @masslive: y.a.’s boyfriend called her names, pulled her hair, and punched her. he took her bank card and only let her use it in his presence, then emptied her bank account, so y.a. couldn’t pay rent. finally, after the man choked y.a. to prevent her from leaving the house, she broke up with him.

y.a. told her landlord at the boston housing authority about the abuse and asked for time to make her payments. but y.a. had by that time negotiated multiple payment plans with the housing authority. the housing authority moved to evict her, and a housing court judge ruled that the authority could go ahead.

the federal violence against women act protects domestic violence victims from eviction, if their inability to pay rent is due to the abuse. the supreme judicial court will hear arguments on monday in the case boston housing authority vs. y.a. about the extent to which these protections apply, and how the federal protections interact with state law.

the court will decide whether y.a., who has two children, can stay in her home. the case could also clarify how public housing landlords and housing courts must treat domestic violence victims who struggle to pay rent. “for victims trying to leave a domestic violence situation, the ability to have safe housing is critical,” said jamie sabino, an attorney with the massachusetts law reform institute who filed an amicus brief with other domestic violence advocates in support of y.a. “were she not to be able to stay in her apartment … and have to try to find a home for herself and her children, there might be a possibility of having to go back to the abuser at some point.” full article: https://www.masslive.com/news/2019/01/does-domestic-violence-protect-a-tenant-from-eviction.html
name: G.R.O.W. Foundation, Inc.

the federal violence against women act protects domestic violence victims from eviction, if their inability to pay rent is due to the abuse. the supreme judicial court will hear arguments on monday in the case boston housing authority vs. y.a. about the extent to which these protections apply, and how the federal protections interact with state law.

the court will decide whether y.a., who has two children, can stay in her home. the case could also clarify how public housing landlords and housing courts must treat domestic violence victims who struggle to pay rent. “for victims trying to leave a domestic violence situation, the ability to have safe housing is critical,” said jamie sabino, an attorney with the massachusetts law reform institute who filed an amicus brief with other domestic violence advocates in support of y.a. “were she not to be able to stay in her apartment … and have to try to find a home for herself and her children, there might be a possibility of having to go back to the abuser at some point.” full article: https://www.masslive.com/news/2019/01/does-domestic-violence-protect-a-tet-from-eviction.html

just in case you forgot what that monster @chrisbrownofficial did to her, i included the photos to refresh your memory. also, he only got 6 months probation and some community service. if you support the artist, you are supporting and enabling the artist’s violent and abusive behavior. #repost @thesweetfeminist
・・・
as you might have seen on my stories, @champagnepapi was my number one streamed artist of 2018 (according to spotify), and i’ve always loved @drakeoncake. so this is an important cake for me to make. yesterday, it was reported that drake is collaborating on an upcoming album with chris brown (who brutally assaulted his then girlfriend rihanna in 2009, among several other assaults). this is bullshit. there are countless examples of privileging a man’s career over the safety of women and girls - there have been two of them showing up in media this week alone (the other being the release of the #survivingrkelly series, which tells the stories of women and girls abused by the singer repeatedly, over many years). 1 in 3 women are survivors of some form of physical violence by an intimate partner. and on average, nearly 20 people per minute are physically abused by an intimate partner in the us (source for both stats: ncadv). intimate partner and domestic violence are not a lower form of violence, and you certainly don’t get a pass for abusing someone you know. for most of us, it’s obvious that it’s unacceptable to abuse. but it seems less universally clear that it’s also unacceptable to try to make excuses for or minimize or explain away or flat out ignore abuses. for anything to change, we all need to stop enabling and making excuses for abusers. and all of us includes drake. #thesweetfeminist #chrisbrown #chrisbrownisanabuser #drake #champaignpapi #rihanna #metoo #domesticviolence #dontbeanenabler #blackgirlsmatter #blacklivesmatter #muterkelly #mutechrisbrown #believewomen #believesurvivors #believevictims #timesup #ageisnotjustanumber #whyididntreport #stockholmsyndrome #emotionalabuse
