text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
watching this @lifetimetv documentary @survivingrkelly has struck something deep in me. i always find myself around people wondering “how,” these things happen? i ironically worked in a domestic violence clinic while being in a psychologically abusive relationship and here’s the kicker that i’ve never shared to anyone beyond my very inner circle...
-
- 
i had never met the man. this quote from the @narcissist.sociopath.awarenes2 account is fitting because i actually paid this woman to help me. (and she did).
-
this particular relationship caused me to attempt suicide, twice. i left law school after 5 semesters of straight a’s because i feared the abuser was in the same city. having a history of other abuses made me an easy victim though i literally was studying things like ”victimology. 🤭”
-
-
i say this in the simplest form because this happened to me (a post-college graduate)  and i was completely controlled and not even in the physical presence of the person... that’s how hard it is to get out. -
-
i went to law enforcement in 3 states. no one does a thing until it’s too late. i went to @mtvcatfish and donna anderson. -
my abuser- khameiah shanae williamson now has a record including endangerment to a minor. (her get in story while posing as a male was she was abused as a child appealing to my empathy). after being in several actual bad relations, one that didn’t involve physicality seemed safe. -
-
she went after my family, friends, professional contacts and continued to far after i got out. no one or thing was off limits. -
-
take a chance and believe the victims. get your people out of situations you know aren’t right. fight the fight. -
thank you to all of you women on this documentary. 
and #muterkelly #timesup #metoo #catfish

text:
el color volvió a la alfombra roja de los #goldenglobes 2019.

la edición pasada de los globos de oro, el movimiento time's up y la reivindicación del #metoo llenaron su alfombra roja de looks en color negro con los que todas las actrices levantaron la voz en defensa de los derechos de las mujeres, tras los escándalos de acoso sexual de harvey weinstein, que habían empañado la industria del cine.

este año, parece que, aunque ambos movimientos siguen latentes no solo en la mente de las actrices, sino de todas las mujeres del mundo, y han prometido seguir presentes en la gala con brazaletes, en los que la diseñadora arianne phillips ha impreso el nombre del movimiento -time's up- multiplicado por dos, y looks negros que no han hecho más que reavivar su recuerdo, los estilismos cargados de color han vuelto a dar de qué hablar.
name: CiudadFoto - Panamá
